                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Greece/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister of Greece presents his compliments to His Excellency the Secretary
                    of State and referring to his <hi rend="italic">Note Verbale</hi> November
                        16,<note n="47" xml:id="d102fn47">
                        <hi rend="italic">Note verbale</hi> of the Greek Minister not
                        printed.</note> has the honor to inform him that, a special mission,
                    consisting of Mr. George Cofinas, former Minister of Finance, and Mr. Michel
                    Evlambios one of the Directors of the National Bank of Greece, will arrive to
                        [<hi rend="italic">in</hi>] Washington, Monday, December the twenty
                        eighth.<note n="48" xml:id="d102fn48">For summary of the negotiations of the
                        Greek mission, see <hi rend="italic">Combined Annual Reports of the World
                            War Foreign Debt Commission</hi>., pp. 76–77.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
